com.datastax.oss.driver.api.core.cql

Interface BoundStatement

  • All Superinterfaces:
    AccessibleById, AccessibleByIndex, AccessibleByName, BatchableStatement<BoundStatement>, Bindable<BoundStatement>, Data, GettableById, GettableByIndex, GettableByName, Request, SettableById<BoundStatement>, SettableByIndex<BoundStatement>, SettableByName<BoundStatement>, Statement<BoundStatement>

    public interface BoundStatement
extends BatchableStatement<BoundStatement>, Bindable<BoundStatement>
    A prepared statement in its executable form, with values bound to the variables.

    The default implementation returned by the driver is immutable and thread-safe. All mutating methods return a new instance.

      • computeSizeInBytes

        default int computeSizeInBytes(@NonNull
                               DriverContext context)
        Description copied from interface: Statement
        Calculates the approximate size in bytes that the statement will have when encoded.

        The size might be over-estimated by a few bytes due to global options that may be defined on a Session but not explicitly set on the statement itself.

        The result of this method is not cached, calling it will cause some encoding to be done in order to determine some of the statement's attributes sizes. Therefore, use this method sparingly in order to avoid unnecessary computation.

        Specified by:
        computeSizeInBytes in interface Statement<BoundStatement>
        Returns:
        the approximate number of bytes this statement will take when encoded.
